1
00:00:03,737 --> 00:00:06,831
911. What's your emergency?
I've got an officer down!

2
00:00:06,906 --> 00:00:10,103
Could you repeat that?
This is Detective Vic Mackey!

3
00:00:10,176 --> 00:00:12,940
An officer's down!
You have an officer down.

4
00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:15,811
The goddamn police radio
in the van isn't working.

5
00:00:15,882 --> 00:00:19,477
What's the officer's condition?
Condition? He's dying!

6
00:00:19,552 --> 00:00:21,816
We're in a...
I have the address.

7
00:00:21,888 --> 00:00:24,823
Where are we?
An ambulance is en route.

8
00:00:24,891 --> 00:00:26,290
I'm coming!

9
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:27,485
Detective?

10
00:00:28,228 --> 00:00:29,456
Detective?

11
00:00:29,796 --> 00:00:32,663
He was about 10, 15 feet
in front of me and Shane...

12
00:00:32,732 --> 00:00:35,462
...when I hear this gunshot,
and I see Terry go down.

13
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:36,695
Jesus.

14
00:00:36,936 --> 00:00:40,394
Shane and I turn the corner,
and we see the guy in this back bathroom.

15
00:00:40,473 --> 00:00:43,067
He gets off a few rounds. We hit back.

16
00:00:43,777 --> 00:00:45,768
At least you killed the prick.

17
00:00:47,147 --> 00:00:48,136
Hey.

18
00:00:48,348 --> 00:00:51,112
Terry's a tough son of a bitch.
He's gonna be okay.

19
00:00:59,793 --> 00:01:01,283
What happened?

20
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,698
- Terry's down?
- Yeah.

21
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:10,367
How is he?
Took a head shot.

22
00:01:11,137 --> 00:01:12,229
Yeah.

23
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:22,510
I didn't clear the room.

24
00:01:22,849 --> 00:01:25,818
I was point.
The first thing you do is clear the room.

25
00:01:25,885 --> 00:01:27,443
We both missed him.

26
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:44,102
At 1:29 a.m., Detective Terry Crowley...

27
00:01:44,304 --> 00:01:47,603
...was admitted for a single
gunshot wound to the face.

28
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:50,107
Surgeons made...

29
00:01:51,678 --> 00:01:53,703
...every attempt to resuscitate him.

30
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,008
Shit.

31
00:01:55,982 --> 00:01:58,917
Ultimately,
their attempts were unsuccessful.

32
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:03,188
Detective Crowley was pronounced dead
at 2:13 this morning.

33
00:02:07,594 --> 00:02:08,652
No!

34
00:02:09,996 --> 00:02:10,985
Damn.

35
00:02:21,941 --> 00:02:23,306
I'm responsible.

36
00:02:40,425 --> 00:02:41,983
I'm responsible.

37
00:02:42,127 --> 00:02:43,890
Responsible how?

38
00:02:43,962 --> 00:02:46,192
It was my operation, and I called the shots.

39
00:02:46,431 --> 00:02:48,661
What could you have done differently?

40
00:02:48,767 --> 00:02:50,564
Terry asked me to move him up.

41
00:02:50,636 --> 00:02:53,434
- He was part of your team.
- He wasn't ready for this.

42
00:02:53,505 --> 00:02:56,804
Eight years as a cop,
a stint in robbery, two commendations.

43
00:02:56,875 --> 00:03:00,242
Sounds to me like he was ready.
Strike Team's different.

44
00:03:00,445 --> 00:03:01,605
Really?

45
00:03:01,713 --> 00:03:04,705
We knock down the doors
other cops don't want to.

46
00:03:05,117 --> 00:03:08,780
My guys accept the risk
because they know I will take care of them.

47
00:03:09,855 --> 00:03:13,621
We go out on a mission, I expect
every single one of them to come home.

48
00:03:14,626 --> 00:03:16,685
Anything else is unacceptable.

49
00:03:19,398 --> 00:03:22,060
Why so long?
They're asking questions.

50
00:03:22,134 --> 00:03:24,432
Yeah, how many questions can they have?

51
00:03:24,503 --> 00:03:27,768
How would it look if I.A.D.
only took five minutes to decide?

52
00:03:27,839 --> 00:03:29,170
They have to be thorough.

53
00:03:29,241 --> 00:03:31,505
Aceveda's gonna use
this to shut us down.

54
00:03:31,577 --> 00:03:34,307
Aceveda's a water boy. He can't do dick.

55
00:03:34,379 --> 00:03:35,971
Why is it taking him so long?

56
00:03:36,048 --> 00:03:38,573
This is the last time.
I answered your question.

57
00:03:39,284 --> 00:03:40,911
Detective Vendrell.

58
00:03:40,986 --> 00:03:42,578
Yeah, that's me.

59
00:03:45,991 --> 00:03:47,959
Just tell them what happened.

60
00:03:48,794 --> 00:03:49,818
Yeah.

61
00:04:04,109 --> 00:04:05,736
What are you doing back here?

62
00:04:05,811 --> 00:04:07,836
Not our crime scene anymore.

63
00:04:07,913 --> 00:04:11,508
I.A.D. gave us a friendly shove.
You didn't shove back?

64
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:13,210
Assistant Chief Gilroy gave the order.

65
00:04:13,285 --> 00:04:15,446
Gilroy? He's there?
He was.

66
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:19,286
I don't like spending five hours
getting evidence for someone else.

67
00:04:19,358 --> 00:04:21,223
Are we on this case, or aren't we?

68
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,784
David.

69
00:04:22,894 --> 00:04:24,020
Sir.

70
00:04:25,197 --> 00:04:26,596
Your office?

71
00:04:30,135 --> 00:04:32,729
Thanks for your good work this morning,
Claudette.

72
00:04:33,872 --> 00:04:35,737
It hasn't been wasted.

73
00:04:36,274 --> 00:04:37,935
No, just our time.

74
00:04:39,745 --> 00:04:40,905
Sir.

75
00:04:42,814 --> 00:04:44,907
Where the hell were you last night?

76
00:04:45,617 --> 00:04:46,948
What do you mean?

77
00:04:47,019 --> 00:04:49,453
Detective Crowley got shot.
I left you a message.

78
00:04:49,521 --> 00:04:50,749
Yeah, I got it.

79
00:04:50,822 --> 00:04:51,914
So?

80
00:04:52,991 --> 00:04:54,856
You didn't say I had to come down.

81
00:04:55,093 --> 00:04:58,585
I shouldn't have to.
A fellow officer was dying in that hospital.

82
00:04:59,598 --> 00:05:01,361
I said a prayer for him.

83
00:05:02,768 --> 00:05:05,134
A prayer?
Yeah.

84
00:05:05,937 --> 00:05:07,029
What?

85
00:05:07,339 --> 00:05:10,536
I've been on the job for three weeks,
I didn't even know that guy.

86
00:05:10,609 --> 00:05:13,737
Rule number one, he was a cop.

87
00:05:14,146 --> 00:05:15,773
That means you knew him.

88
00:05:19,084 --> 00:05:21,109
Two deaths, two investigations.

89
00:05:21,186 --> 00:05:22,813
David, please.

90
00:05:22,888 --> 00:05:25,948
You can't have your cops
investigating your cops.

91
00:05:26,024 --> 00:05:29,323
If you clear the Strike Team,
that's gonna smack of favoritism.

92
00:05:29,394 --> 00:05:33,057
If you actually find something,
you'll have a civil war on your hands.

93
00:05:33,131 --> 00:05:35,031
Let Internal Affairs do their job.

94
00:05:43,842 --> 00:05:46,640
Has anyone sent Department sympathies
to Crowley's family?

95
00:05:46,712 --> 00:05:48,771
I spoke to his mother an hour ago.

96
00:05:48,847 --> 00:05:51,145
Someone from our side
should speak at the funeral.

97
00:05:51,216 --> 00:05:54,481
Perhaps you...
No. He was your man.

98
00:05:55,454 --> 00:05:57,445
I'm sure you'll represent us well.

99
00:05:58,056 --> 00:06:00,286
You're the first
Mackey brought aboard...

100
00:06:00,358 --> 00:06:02,053
...when he assembled the Strike Team.

101
00:06:02,127 --> 00:06:04,925
- We worked things together.
- So there was a comfort level.

102
00:06:04,996 --> 00:06:06,793
Yeah.
Same with the others?

103
00:06:06,865 --> 00:06:09,561
Vic knew them, too.
Detective Crowley?

104
00:06:09,634 --> 00:06:12,535
No, he was recommended by someone.
I don't recall who.

105
00:06:12,604 --> 00:06:14,162
So Terry was an outsider?

106
00:06:14,239 --> 00:06:17,436
No, he was a new guy,
but once Vic puts you on the team...

107
00:06:17,509 --> 00:06:19,534
...then you're on the team.

108
00:06:22,180 --> 00:06:23,943
Hey.
Hi.

109
00:06:24,983 --> 00:06:26,951
Strike Team's getting the third degree.

110
00:06:27,018 --> 00:06:28,747
Yeah, looks like it.

111
00:06:28,887 --> 00:06:30,718
You're assigned the crime scene, right?

112
00:06:31,189 --> 00:06:32,816
We're off it now.

113
00:06:33,925 --> 00:06:36,723
The guys are curious.
I said I'd find out what's going on.

114
00:06:36,795 --> 00:06:37,955
Any idea?

115
00:06:38,029 --> 00:06:41,897
Looks to me like Vic and his cowboys
went in undermanned with a half-ass plan...

116
00:06:41,967 --> 00:06:44,094
...and managed to get a guy killed.

117
00:06:45,170 --> 00:06:47,161
Then again, I'm off the case.

118
00:06:49,574 --> 00:06:50,836
Later, okay?

119
00:06:51,309 --> 00:06:54,039
Tell him this is L.A., not the Wild West.

120
00:06:59,117 --> 00:07:03,053
- I'd know those fingernails anywhere.
- How you holding up?

121
00:07:03,555 --> 00:07:06,080
I lost a guy. I don't like it.

122
00:07:07,159 --> 00:07:10,287
- I saw you at the hospital last night.
- I saw you, too.

123
00:07:11,062 --> 00:07:14,031
- You had a crowd. I didn't want...
- It's all right.

124
00:07:14,966 --> 00:07:17,867
- Look, I don't want you to think that...
- I don't.

125
00:07:23,642 --> 00:07:27,237
If you need a break from all this
and want to talk, come find me.

126
00:07:27,412 --> 00:07:28,640
That's good to know.

127
00:07:33,952 --> 00:07:36,045
Anytime someone kills a cop...

128
00:07:36,121 --> 00:07:39,522
...scumbags get it into their heads
that it's open season.

129
00:07:39,758 --> 00:07:41,692
- Police rule number...
- Three.

130
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:44,888
Cop goes down, we re-establish
our dominance on the street.

131
00:07:44,963 --> 00:07:47,397
Someone mouths off,
they hit the pavement.

132
00:07:47,733 --> 00:07:50,463
Someone resists,
we make sure they make a pit stop...

133
00:07:50,535 --> 00:07:52,127
...at the emergency room.

134
00:07:53,672 --> 00:07:56,835
We gotta make sure these assholes
know who's in charge. Right?

135
00:07:56,908 --> 00:07:58,273
Loud and clear.

136
00:07:58,577 --> 00:08:00,044
What happened to your hand?

137
00:08:00,112 --> 00:08:01,602
I put it through a window.

138
00:08:02,514 --> 00:08:04,175
Last night during the raid?

139
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:06,782
No. After, when I found out about Terry.

140
00:08:07,285 --> 00:08:08,718
Is it all right?

141
00:08:09,121 --> 00:08:10,053
Yeah.

142
00:08:10,122 --> 00:08:13,023
Cut up pretty bad, though.
Any tendon damage?

143
00:08:13,425 --> 00:08:16,019
Can we just get this
the hell over with, please?

144
00:08:25,570 --> 00:08:29,028
Mackey sent Terry to get killed.
You don't know that.

145
00:08:29,107 --> 00:08:30,233
Please.

146
00:08:30,542 --> 00:08:32,806
Cops get killed in the line of duty.

147
00:08:32,878 --> 00:08:35,972
Did you tell anyone
Terry was trying to take down Mackey?

148
00:08:36,047 --> 00:08:36,877
Did you?

149
00:08:36,948 --> 00:08:39,576
David...
I didn't, and Terry's dead.

150
00:08:39,651 --> 00:08:40,948
I followed protocol.

151
00:08:41,019 --> 00:08:42,350
Protocol.

152
00:08:42,821 --> 00:08:47,087
Things that Terry wanted, a job,
a car, I'm not authorized to sign off on.

153
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:50,822
So you broke the circle.
I sent his requests up the ladder.

154
00:08:50,996 --> 00:08:54,363
This is the Justice Department.
So they can be trusted?

155
00:08:54,432 --> 00:08:56,900
I've got to go to I.A.D.
Why?

156
00:08:56,968 --> 00:08:59,766
To let them know
exactly why Mackey wanted Terry dead.

157
00:08:59,838 --> 00:09:02,773
You can't do that.
They'll let him walk, Moses.

158
00:09:02,841 --> 00:09:05,173
If they have motive, they'll dig deeper.

159
00:09:05,243 --> 00:09:09,543
You initiated an off-the-books
investigation into one of your own men.

160
00:09:09,781 --> 00:09:11,840
You come forward, your career's dead.

161
00:09:11,950 --> 00:09:14,043
We sent Terry to his own death.

162
00:09:14,119 --> 00:09:15,746
What am I supposed to do?

163
00:09:15,821 --> 00:09:18,153
What do you hope to accomplish?

164
00:09:18,356 --> 00:09:20,756
It won't prove that Vic set Terry up.

165
00:09:21,126 --> 00:09:24,527
You'll lose the power
you've worked your whole life to acquire.

166
00:09:25,797 --> 00:09:27,890
I'm not gonna let him get away with it.

167
00:09:32,504 --> 00:09:35,735
There is an epitaph
for an unknown soldier that goes:

168
00:09:35,807 --> 00:09:37,604
"Do not stand on my grave and weep

169
00:09:37,676 --> 00:09:40,167
"For I am not there, I do not sleep.

170
00:09:40,879 --> 00:09:43,507
"With my brothers in the field, I kneel

171
00:09:43,582 --> 00:09:45,447
"Their lives, my merit

172
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:47,174
"My death, their zeal."

173
00:09:48,653 --> 00:09:50,553
I believe these words do express...

174
00:09:51,022 --> 00:09:53,456
...the sentiments
of Detective Terry Crowley.

175
00:09:53,959 --> 00:09:56,792
A good man and an
exemplary police officer...

176
00:09:56,862 --> 00:09:59,626
...who served his community
and his department...

177
00:09:59,698 --> 00:10:03,134
...with dignity, loyalty, and courage.

178
00:10:04,669 --> 00:10:07,729
In the brief time that
I was fortunate enough to work with him...

179
00:10:07,806 --> 00:10:10,536
...I came to know him
as a man who embraced life...

180
00:10:11,109 --> 00:10:13,304
...adored his friends and family...

181
00:10:14,145 --> 00:10:15,669
...and loved being a cop.

182
00:10:16,014 --> 00:10:18,244
"I am the resurrection and the light.

183
00:10:19,451 --> 00:10:21,214
"He that believeth in me

184
00:10:21,453 --> 00:10:23,216
"Even though he were dead

185
00:10:23,288 --> 00:10:24,277
"Yet, shall he live."

186
00:10:24,356 --> 00:10:26,347
Amen.
Yes, Lord.

187
00:10:26,424 --> 00:10:29,154
"The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

188
00:10:29,227 --> 00:10:32,162
"He maketh me to lie down
in green pastures

189
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:34,289
"He leadeth me beside the still waters."

190
00:10:34,366 --> 00:10:37,233
We will miss his service
and his good nature.

191
00:10:38,403 --> 00:10:41,770
And I know I speak
on behalf of the entire force when I say...

192
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:44,900
...Terry, our lives are your merit...

193
00:10:46,044 --> 00:10:48,444
...and your memory gives us zeal.

194
00:10:50,448 --> 00:10:52,973
"He leadeth me beside the still waters.

195
00:10:53,051 --> 00:10:54,916
"He restoreth my soul.

196
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:58,155
"Yea, though I walk through the valley
of the shadow of death

197
00:10:58,223 --> 00:10:59,713
"I will fear no evil

198
00:10:59,925 --> 00:11:01,324
"For thou art with me

199
00:11:01,393 --> 00:11:04,521
"Thy rod and thy staff, they comfort me."

200
00:11:06,865 --> 00:11:08,059
Fire!

201
00:11:09,601 --> 00:11:10,590
Fire!

202
00:11:14,239 --> 00:11:18,141
Baby, I'm sorry! Mama's sorry!
It's all right, now.

203
00:11:18,209 --> 00:11:21,610
Mama's sorry, baby!
It's gonna be all right.

204
00:11:26,451 --> 00:11:27,975
What are you doing?

205
00:11:28,053 --> 00:11:30,749
- What?
- Save it for the car ride, Shane.

206
00:11:31,189 --> 00:11:32,918
What's the matter with you?

207
00:11:32,991 --> 00:11:36,358
- I didn't expect to see his mother here...
- He had a mom. So what?

208
00:11:36,428 --> 00:11:38,396
So what did we do?

209
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:40,528
What we had to.

210
00:11:40,598 --> 00:11:43,761
- Christ, come on, man.
- Enough. Come on.

211
00:11:43,835 --> 00:11:45,200
I'm cold, man.

212
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:48,967
Look, we made him one of us,
and what did he do?

213
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:51,406
- What did he do?
- He turned rat.

214
00:11:51,476 --> 00:11:53,410
He tried to stick us both in a cage...

215
00:11:53,478 --> 00:11:56,106
...with the same goddamn animals
we fight every day.

216
00:11:56,181 --> 00:11:58,342
Now, did I enjoy it? No.

217
00:11:58,483 --> 00:12:02,180
Did it need to be done?
You're goddamn right it did.

218
00:12:02,854 --> 00:12:04,446
Now, listen to me...

219
00:12:06,358 --> 00:12:08,485
...we're gonna ride this out. Right?

220
00:12:10,762 --> 00:12:12,457
I'm so sorry for your loss.

221
00:12:38,389 --> 00:12:41,085
Sir, step back.
It's cool. I called you.

222
00:12:41,159 --> 00:12:43,787
- Step away from the body.
- I need the money he owes me.

223
00:12:43,862 --> 00:12:45,420
Don't make me warn you again.

224
00:12:45,497 --> 00:12:48,489
He's got my cash.
I'm not gonna warn you again.

225
00:12:48,566 --> 00:12:51,433
I need the money he owes me.
What'd she say?

226
00:12:51,569 --> 00:12:53,332
Let's go!
What?

227
00:12:56,808 --> 00:12:58,241
I'm a good Samaritan here!

228
00:12:58,309 --> 00:13:00,072
What were you doing to the body?

229
00:13:00,145 --> 00:13:02,113
I heard he had the $100 he owed me...

230
00:13:02,180 --> 00:13:04,273
...so I come here
and see somebody shot him!

231
00:13:04,349 --> 00:13:07,045
So I went down the block
and called for 911...

232
00:13:07,118 --> 00:13:09,245
...and come back here to get my money.

233
00:13:09,387 --> 00:13:12,686
Jesus, Julien, this guy's still alive.
This is 1-Tango-13.

234
00:13:12,757 --> 00:13:14,952
I need a R.A. to respond.

235
00:13:15,026 --> 00:13:16,425
Keep fighting, man!

236
00:13:16,494 --> 00:13:19,292
- Keep fighting! I'll collect from you later!
- Let's go.

237
00:13:32,710 --> 00:13:36,271
Shane barely touched his pork chops.
I don't think he's doing well.

238
00:13:36,347 --> 00:13:39,009
He's gonna be fine.
He don't seem fine.

239
00:13:39,083 --> 00:13:40,812
It hasn't even been a week yet.

240
00:13:41,853 --> 00:13:43,445
I'm coming, sweetie.

241
00:13:44,189 --> 00:13:46,885
It's like he blames himself
for the whole thing.

242
00:13:46,958 --> 00:13:50,359
It's not normal.
I mean, it's not like he killed Terry.

243
00:14:07,545 --> 00:14:08,569
Ace of clubs.

244
00:14:08,646 --> 00:14:11,137
I'm sitting poolside
with this guy named Frank...

245
00:14:11,216 --> 00:14:13,047
- Transvestite?
- He's buying drinks.

246
00:14:13,117 --> 00:14:14,345
That ugly one?

247
00:14:14,419 --> 00:14:16,683
Yeah, the guy that I always hang out with.

248
00:14:16,888 --> 00:14:19,482
50 years old!
You gotta be joking me!

249
00:14:19,691 --> 00:14:21,556
You holding out on me, Shane?

