499
00:27:25,674 --> 00:27:27,164
What was that all about?

500
00:27:27,242 --> 00:27:30,006
Aceveda is spinning his wheels, as usual.

501
00:27:32,614 --> 00:27:33,774
Enter.

502
00:27:35,884 --> 00:27:39,251
What can you tell me
about a new gang called Los Magnificos?

503
00:27:39,321 --> 00:27:41,312
They're not so new...

504
00:27:41,390 --> 00:27:44,450
...they been clawing up the food chain
for the last six months.

505
00:27:44,526 --> 00:27:48,155
Someone from the gang
pulled the trigger on my churro guy.

506
00:27:48,230 --> 00:27:49,857
Any bushes you can beat?

507
00:27:50,499 --> 00:27:53,229
Looks like we've been invited
to the party, ladies.

508
00:27:53,602 --> 00:27:54,728
Let's go.

509
00:27:57,072 --> 00:27:58,903
I hear it's your birthday.

510
00:27:59,775 --> 00:28:01,333
Happy birthday.

511
00:28:03,679 --> 00:28:05,647
I need to ask Shane a few questions.

512
00:28:05,714 --> 00:28:08,182
Me?
I need 10 minutes.

513
00:28:08,250 --> 00:28:10,343
I'll send him to catch up with you.

514
00:28:10,719 --> 00:28:11,708
I'm cool.

515
00:28:11,787 --> 00:28:14,085
I'm gonna grab a Coke first.
Do you need anything?

516
00:28:14,156 --> 00:28:15,487
No.

517
00:28:29,371 --> 00:28:30,702
How's the paint brush, Van Bro?

518
00:28:30,773 --> 00:28:33,298
Don't be coming around here
unless you lookin' to buy.

519
00:28:33,375 --> 00:28:34,740
And no more freebies.

520
00:28:34,810 --> 00:28:37,472
You want info,
you have to buy something this time.

521
00:28:37,546 --> 00:28:38,478
All right.

522
00:28:38,781 --> 00:28:42,273
- Lem, pick the poison.
- What do I know about art, man?

523
00:28:42,751 --> 00:28:43,911
Ronnie?

524
00:28:45,954 --> 00:28:47,888
I like the one with the clouds.

525
00:28:47,956 --> 00:28:49,856
You got a place for it?

526
00:28:50,092 --> 00:28:51,457
Yeah, I guess.

527
00:28:51,693 --> 00:28:53,456
All right. How much?

528
00:28:54,430 --> 00:28:56,022
Gimme $100.

529
00:28:58,367 --> 00:29:01,336
And don't be hangin' it
in no bathroom, neither.

530
00:29:03,705 --> 00:29:06,765
Looking for a Los Mag.
Shot up a churro vendor.

531
00:29:10,612 --> 00:29:13,342
The people say
amigo didn't want to pay his freight.

532
00:29:13,415 --> 00:29:15,212
He ignored a couple of warnings.

533
00:29:15,284 --> 00:29:18,253
Los Mags sent in a baby banger
to do the dirty deed.

534
00:29:19,054 --> 00:29:20,954
Earned him his stripes.

535
00:29:21,757 --> 00:29:23,384
Initiation shooting?

536
00:29:23,625 --> 00:29:25,957
Things they got these kids doing.

537
00:29:26,462 --> 00:29:30,023
Did you have to bake a batch
of brownies back in your day, Van Bro?

538
00:29:31,099 --> 00:29:34,296
Getting into life was a lot more fun
than getting out.

539
00:29:34,503 --> 00:29:36,767
I heard you lost a man a few days back.

540
00:29:37,639 --> 00:29:40,301
- Yeah.
- Tough times, Vic.

541
00:29:40,943 --> 00:29:43,138
I don't know. Maybe someday...

542
00:29:43,479 --> 00:29:45,447
...somebody even win this war.

543
00:29:45,514 --> 00:29:46,947
I intend to.

544
00:29:47,783 --> 00:29:50,479
VAN See you around, baby.
All right, man.

545
00:30:01,330 --> 00:30:03,855
This little vato ready for the barrio?

546
00:30:15,344 --> 00:30:18,541
The wannabe getting initiated,
he's our shooter.

547
00:30:18,614 --> 00:30:19,603
I'll take him.

548
00:30:19,681 --> 00:30:22,582
Anybody else gets caught in our net,
it's gravy.

549
00:30:22,684 --> 00:30:25,847
- Are we goin' in?
- No. His punk ass wants a beating.

550
00:30:25,921 --> 00:30:27,786
I say we let him have it.

551
00:30:38,367 --> 00:30:39,664
What's he saying?

552
00:30:39,902 --> 00:30:41,665
"Welcome to the life."

553
00:30:50,612 --> 00:30:52,307
You were going to be his backup.

554
00:30:52,381 --> 00:30:53,541
We were his backup.

555
00:30:53,615 --> 00:30:55,583
Why is Terry dead, then?

556
00:30:55,851 --> 00:30:57,478
Wrong place, wrong time.

557
00:30:57,553 --> 00:31:01,649
Aren't you and Vic supposed to be
these kick-ass top cops?

558
00:31:02,824 --> 00:31:05,019
How does somebody you're backing up...

559
00:31:05,093 --> 00:31:06,928
...get blown away by some
pissant drug dealer?

560
00:31:06,929 --> 00:31:07,656
...get blown away by some
pissant drug dealer?

561
00:31:08,195 --> 00:31:09,822
I.A.D. cleared us.

562
00:31:09,897 --> 00:31:11,421
I didn't clear you.

563
00:31:12,533 --> 00:31:14,262
It just went bad. That's all.

564
00:31:15,303 --> 00:31:16,395
You lie.

565
00:31:16,470 --> 00:31:19,030
He squints when he lies.
You do.

566
00:31:19,106 --> 00:31:21,734
No, I don't.
You're squinting now.

567
00:31:40,695 --> 00:31:42,356
All right. Play time's over.

568
00:31:42,430 --> 00:31:44,990
Last one down the hill
gets to drink the backwash.

569
00:31:45,066 --> 00:31:48,297
All right. We're a go in three, two, one, go!

570
00:31:48,803 --> 00:31:49,792
Go.

571
00:31:59,747 --> 00:32:01,044
Police!

572
00:32:01,115 --> 00:32:02,582
Stop right there! Freeze!

573
00:32:24,438 --> 00:32:26,167
Bienvenido a la vida.

574
00:32:38,519 --> 00:32:40,419
You let Terry get killed.

575
00:32:40,488 --> 00:32:42,979
Why would we do that?
You know why.

576
00:32:43,891 --> 00:32:45,222
I.A.D. cleared us.

577
00:32:48,996 --> 00:32:51,191
You know a drug dealer
named Rondell Robinson?

578
00:32:51,265 --> 00:32:52,232
No.

579
00:32:52,366 --> 00:32:54,027
You're squinting. You don't know him?

580
00:32:55,002 --> 00:32:56,526
I know who he is.

581
00:32:56,804 --> 00:32:58,738
I meant I don't know him personally.

582
00:32:58,806 --> 00:33:03,106
So if I had a witness that saw you and Vic
acting real friendly with Rondell Robinson...

583
00:33:03,477 --> 00:33:04,705
...that would be a lie.

584
00:33:04,779 --> 00:33:05,837
That's right.

585
00:33:05,913 --> 00:33:08,143
So he didn't see
the three of you at a car wash?

586
00:33:14,155 --> 00:33:16,749
Vic was just puttin' a scare into him.

587
00:33:16,824 --> 00:33:19,486
Lettin' him know
that we were watching him.

588
00:33:19,560 --> 00:33:21,528
So you lied.
No, I didn't.

589
00:33:21,595 --> 00:33:23,529
I meant something else.

590
00:33:23,597 --> 00:33:26,862
Terry knew you were
in bed with Robinson, so he had to die.

591
00:33:26,934 --> 00:33:28,094
Terry was in our team.

592
00:33:28,169 --> 00:33:29,864
He was your errand boy.

593
00:33:29,937 --> 00:33:32,565
Bullshit.
You led Terry there to die.

594
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,664
Not true.

595
00:33:33,741 --> 00:33:35,606
The one guy who disapproved...

596
00:33:35,676 --> 00:33:39,612
...is the only one who didn't come out
of that house alive. That's a coincidence?

597
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,011
Believe what you want.

598
00:33:41,148 --> 00:33:43,582
Terry was gonna turn you in,
so Vic wanted him dead.

599
00:33:43,651 --> 00:33:45,778
- Vic needed him dead!
- No!

600
00:33:48,556 --> 00:33:49,818
God.

601
00:33:50,491 --> 00:33:51,719
The shot.

602
00:33:52,059 --> 00:33:55,153
- That's what the last shot was.
- The last shot?

603
00:33:55,229 --> 00:33:58,721
Two-Time's girlfriend said
that she heard the last shot...

604
00:33:58,799 --> 00:34:00,960
...10, 15 seconds after the others.

605
00:34:01,969 --> 00:34:04,767
When we approached Two-Time, he moved.

606
00:34:05,840 --> 00:34:07,535
Vic couldn't leave it to chance.

607
00:34:08,042 --> 00:34:11,478
Vic fired once more.
That's the shot that killed Terry.

608
00:34:11,545 --> 00:34:13,877
- No way.
- Vic fired that shot, didn't he?

609
00:34:13,948 --> 00:34:16,041
- No.
- Stop squinting!

610
00:34:17,518 --> 00:34:18,746
I know.

611
00:34:19,954 --> 00:34:21,080
I know.

612
00:34:30,631 --> 00:34:31,962
You're wrong.

613
00:34:34,301 --> 00:34:35,666
I want Mackey.

614
00:34:35,769 --> 00:34:39,034
- You don't have to go down with him.
- That is not how it happened.

615
00:34:39,106 --> 00:34:42,075
Stop lying to me.
I know what happened.

616
00:34:43,611 --> 00:34:45,044
I have a witness, Shane.

617
00:34:46,313 --> 00:34:48,645
He connects you and Vic
with Rondell Robinson.

618
00:34:48,716 --> 00:34:50,479
I have a witness.

619
00:34:52,086 --> 00:34:54,281
Give me Vic and your problems end.

620
00:34:56,957 --> 00:34:58,686
Just give me Mackey.

621
00:35:02,830 --> 00:35:06,095
What the hell's going on here?
You've had him here for two hours?

622
00:35:06,167 --> 00:35:09,568
He's making up sick shit about us.
Wait for me downstairs.

623
00:35:09,737 --> 00:35:13,468
This whole thing is a joke.
Grab a sandwich, Dutch-boy.

624
00:35:20,581 --> 00:35:22,276
I know what you did.

625
00:35:24,418 --> 00:35:26,352
Up until now, I've tolerated you.

626
00:35:27,555 --> 00:35:31,355
You come near my men again,
I'm gonna lose patience.

627
00:35:32,359 --> 00:35:33,792
You listening?

628
00:35:36,931 --> 00:35:38,091
I know.

629
00:35:51,212 --> 00:35:55,012
The churro guy you shot's
in surgery. They don't know if he'll live.

630
00:35:55,083 --> 00:35:56,948
Tell her you didn't shoot this man.

631
00:35:57,018 --> 00:36:01,079
If you tell me who had you
do this, I might get you into juvie court.

632
00:36:01,155 --> 00:36:05,091
If you wait and he dies,
you'll be tried for murder as an adult.

633
00:36:05,159 --> 00:36:07,354
Please tell her you didn't do this.

634
00:36:07,428 --> 00:36:09,396
Of course I didn't.
You see?

635
00:36:09,464 --> 00:36:12,797
I shoot someone,
he don't almost end up dead.

636
00:36:12,867 --> 00:36:14,459
Bitch ends up all dead.

637
00:36:16,137 --> 00:36:19,470
That's your alibi?
If you'd have shot him, he'd be dead?

638
00:36:19,540 --> 00:36:21,132
Hell, yeah. That's my alibi.

639
00:36:29,650 --> 00:36:33,211
Guess what?
Churro guy's actually gonna make it.

640
00:36:33,554 --> 00:36:34,612
Good.

641
00:36:34,689 --> 00:36:38,125
You're not gonna believe what went down
between Aceveda and Mackey.

642
00:36:38,192 --> 00:36:40,820
- I don't want to know.
- Yeah, I know, but this is...

643
00:36:40,895 --> 00:36:42,658
Anyone gets between those two...

644
00:36:42,730 --> 00:36:46,530
...will end up with a hose full of piss
running down his leg.

645
00:36:50,271 --> 00:36:52,398
Good news and bad news.

646
00:36:53,741 --> 00:36:55,231
Bad news is...

647
00:36:56,644 --> 00:36:59,010
...the churro vendor just died.

648
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:03,449
Good news for your son, though,
someone else is taking credit for the killing.

649
00:37:03,985 --> 00:37:05,179
Thank you, Jesus.

650
00:37:05,253 --> 00:37:08,222
Some guy named Marlon
walked in off the street...

651
00:37:08,356 --> 00:37:11,382
...said your gang was trying
to muscle in on his business...

652
00:37:11,459 --> 00:37:15,020
...so he decided to show all the vendors
your gang couldn't protect them.

653
00:37:15,096 --> 00:37:16,324
Marlon didn't do no shooting.

654
00:37:16,397 --> 00:37:20,231
He did. Everyone's talking
about how he showed your boys up.

655
00:37:20,301 --> 00:37:22,792
That old man stopped paying us.
That's my shooting!

656
00:37:22,870 --> 00:37:25,361
- He's just looking to piggyback a rep.
- Olman, no.

657
00:37:25,439 --> 00:37:27,964
You're trying
to take credit for it now?

658
00:37:28,042 --> 00:37:31,102
- Stop...
- I told you if I shot him, he'd be dead, right?

659
00:37:31,179 --> 00:37:32,908
People need to know.

660
00:37:33,114 --> 00:37:34,672
Los Mags own these streets.

661
00:37:35,650 --> 00:37:39,086
- Who asked you to do the shooting?
- I ain't never telling you that.

662
00:37:40,588 --> 00:37:42,021
These are my brothers now.

663
00:37:42,356 --> 00:37:44,290
Do you know what this means?

664
00:37:44,358 --> 00:37:45,825
Means I earned my way in.

665
00:37:45,893 --> 00:37:48,691
No. It means you're going to jail.

666
00:37:55,469 --> 00:37:57,164
At least I'll have family there.

667
00:38:09,483 --> 00:38:12,646
Tell me you didn't reopen an investigation
that wasn't even yours.

668
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:14,119
There were unanswered questions.

669
00:38:14,188 --> 00:38:16,713
You accused Mackey
of working with a drug dealer.

670
00:38:16,791 --> 00:38:19,191
- Who's your witness?
- Anonymous tip.

671
00:38:19,260 --> 00:38:21,125
Anyone who can corroborate it?

672
00:38:24,999 --> 00:38:29,129
Is there something I don't know
that explains why you're still pursuing this?

673
00:38:31,772 --> 00:38:32,761
Well?

674
00:38:34,842 --> 00:38:35,866
No.

675
00:38:36,377 --> 00:38:38,004
Then it ends here.

676
00:38:40,848 --> 00:38:42,315
Christ, David.

677
00:38:44,185 --> 00:38:45,880
You're doing a good job.

678
00:38:46,254 --> 00:38:48,119
Chief said so the other day.

679
00:38:50,391 --> 00:38:51,881
Don't lose focus now.

680
00:38:52,827 --> 00:38:53,851
I won't.

681
00:38:55,396 --> 00:38:56,522
Good.

682
00:38:56,764 --> 00:38:59,358
Thanks for getting
Captain Ass-lnvader off my back.

683
00:38:59,433 --> 00:39:02,129
It wouldn't kill you
to show him more respect.

684
00:39:02,203 --> 00:39:03,261
Come on.

685
00:39:03,337 --> 00:39:05,703
Vic, the men here take their cues from you.

686
00:39:05,773 --> 00:39:07,468
I'm just saying dial it down.

687
00:39:07,541 --> 00:39:10,374
I don't do my best work
with him nipping at my heels.

688
00:39:10,444 --> 00:39:13,607
- Which is why I'm watching out for you.
- Good.

689
00:39:13,681 --> 00:39:15,945
Question is, are you watching out for me?

690
00:39:16,384 --> 00:39:17,578
Meaning?

691
00:39:17,685 --> 00:39:20,620
My guys tipped you off
that Terry was looking to take you down.

692
00:39:20,688 --> 00:39:24,886
- Ben, the bust just went bad.
- My source at Justice is all over my ass.

693
00:39:24,959 --> 00:39:28,224
He wants to know if you made us
all accomplices to a murder.

694
00:39:28,996 --> 00:39:32,397
I told him you'd never do that to me.

695
00:39:34,902 --> 00:39:36,028
Would you?

696
00:39:39,273 --> 00:39:41,867
Terry got overeager. He got himself killed.

697
00:39:43,611 --> 00:39:44,908
End of story?

698
00:39:45,579 --> 00:39:47,046
End of story.

699
00:39:50,451 --> 00:39:51,918
It better be.

700
00:40:04,965 --> 00:40:06,523
Is this from you?

701
00:40:07,435 --> 00:40:11,166
No. I know how you feel about birthdays.

702
00:40:16,544 --> 00:40:17,943
Denture cream.

703
00:40:19,980 --> 00:40:21,106
Thank you.

704
00:40:22,116 --> 00:40:23,981
'Cause I'm getting old.

705
00:40:25,152 --> 00:40:26,881
I don't see a card.

706
00:40:26,954 --> 00:40:29,184
Anyone want to take credit for this?

707
00:40:29,623 --> 00:40:32,353
Not me.
I didn't think so.

708
00:40:33,227 --> 00:40:36,196
- How's the birthday girl doing?
- Don't say that word.

709
00:40:36,263 --> 00:40:39,494
- I came to take you dancing.
- I don't want to go dancing.

710
00:40:39,567 --> 00:40:41,432
Now we gotta do something, honey.

711
00:40:41,502 --> 00:40:43,732
It's your birthday.
So?

712
00:40:43,804 --> 00:40:46,898
So, it's ladies night at the Crimson.

713
00:40:48,109 --> 00:40:52,341
I have it on very good authority
that Franklin Green's gonna be there.

714
00:40:55,516 --> 00:40:58,178
- His divorce final?
- Two weeks ago.

715
00:41:04,458 --> 00:41:07,586
I can't let Franklin Green
see me looking like this.

716
00:41:07,661 --> 00:41:10,721
Which is why we'll spruce up first,
then go to the Crimson.

717
00:41:10,798 --> 00:41:14,598
- We too old to be chasing men around.
- I'm not.

718
00:41:14,668 --> 00:41:16,568
Neither am I. Come on.

719
00:41:19,173 --> 00:41:22,609
Drink! Drink! Drink! Drink!

720
00:41:26,013 --> 00:41:28,538
Who said that Jesus freak couldn't drink?

721
00:41:30,684 --> 00:41:32,675
Your b-and-b's almost complete, buddy boy.

722
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:35,384
You had the beer.
Now it's time for the blow.

723
00:41:36,590 --> 00:41:38,785
- You're kidding.
- I kid you not.

724
00:41:38,859 --> 00:41:40,520
She's a badge sucker.

725
00:41:42,029 --> 00:41:43,428
What's a badge sucker?

726
00:41:43,497 --> 00:41:45,965
A badge sucker, man.
She digs cops, okay?

727
00:41:46,033 --> 00:41:49,127
She's like the neighborhood
welcoming committee. Listen.

728
00:41:49,203 --> 00:41:51,569
A better hummer you're not gonna find.

729
00:41:51,639 --> 00:41:53,106
- Trust me.
- No...

730
00:41:53,307 --> 00:41:56,538
I cannot...
No, stay, listen!

731
00:41:56,610 --> 00:41:58,009
Sit down!

732
00:41:58,078 --> 00:42:01,206
This isn't torture, okay?
We've all gone through this.

733
00:42:01,882 --> 00:42:03,782
Julien, say hi to Betty.

734
00:42:04,385 --> 00:42:07,684
So this is the new guy?
Go!

735
00:42:09,323 --> 00:42:11,018
Welcome to the force.

736
00:42:12,059 --> 00:42:14,527
Handsome.
And he's lucky, too.

737
00:42:15,229 --> 00:42:19,256
Wanna go for a walk?
Fellas, I cannot. No.

738
00:42:20,801 --> 00:42:22,530
Come on, now. I can't!

739
00:42:22,803 --> 00:42:23,792
Go!

740
00:42:29,243 --> 00:42:30,801
Give it up, man.

741
00:42:35,216 --> 00:42:36,843
Wait. Come on.

742
00:42:37,451 --> 00:42:39,248
Come on.
All right.

743
00:42:40,454 --> 00:42:42,354
Let's get you over here.

744
00:42:42,556 --> 00:42:44,148
Relax, Officer.

745
00:42:44,959 --> 00:42:47,052
This is a lot more fun than roll call.

746
00:42:53,100 --> 00:42:54,931
You don't have to do this.

747
00:43:13,787 --> 00:43:15,254
Yeah.

748
00:43:19,260 --> 00:43:21,285
She love him long time.

749
00:43:22,596 --> 00:43:23,824
Go!

